Cut the cauliflower into florets and pulse in a food processor until it resembles rice grains.

Heat sesame oil in a large skillet over medium heat.

Add the riced cauliflower to the skillet and sauté for 5-7 minutes until it's tender but not mushy.

Stir in rice vinegar and soy sauce. Remove from heat and set aside.

2. Cook the Shrimp:

In a separate skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.

Season the shrimp with salt and black pepper.

Add the shrimp to the skillet and cook for 2-3 minutes per side or until they are pink and opaque.

Optional: Sprinkle sesame seeds over the cooked shrimp for added flavor and texture.

3. Assemble the Sushi Bowl:

Divide the cauliflower rice among serving bowls.

Arrange sliced avocado, julienned cucumber, and julienned carrot on top of the cauliflower rice.

Place the cooked shrimp on one side of the bowl.

Garnish with sliced nori.

4. Serve:

Serve the Low-Carb Shrimp Sushi Bowl with soy sauce or tamari on the side.

Optionally, serve with pickled ginger and wasabi."
